text: - I am Rieah,

and I'm an Associate
Solutions Architect for AWS.
Prior to AWS, I was a student.
I had done some software development,
so like a year in industry,
but I did computer science
with artificial intelligence at uni,

and this is my first job
straight out of uni, so yeah.

My honest favorite part
about the role is the people.
At first, it can be a bit scary
because you're around a lot of people

that know a lot of things,
and, slowly but surely,
you realize that you're one of the people
that know a lot of things, too.
We do the impossible a lot here.
There are things that somebody asks me,
and I look at it off the bat,
and I'm like, (laughs) "I don't know."
And you find a way to do it.
And you get the feeling of like,

about to jump off like
a bungee jump, right?

You get that feeling of like,
"Oh, what if it goes wrong?"

But you kinda know that
you've got the wire there
because you're allowed to take risk.
(upbeat music)
